00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.508 line:0%
 
JIM THORPE
WAS A NATIVE-AMERICAN.

00:00:07.608 --> 00:00:11.745 line:0%
 
HE ENTERED
CARLISLE HIGH SCHOOL IN 1907.

00:00:11.845 --> 00:00:14.014
HE WAS THE BEST
AT FOOTBALL.

00:00:14.114 --> 00:00:15.482
THE BEST.

00:00:15.582 --> 00:00:18.785
HIS COACH, POP WARNER,
WAS SAYING,

00:00:18.886 --> 00:00:21.221
YOU KNOW, YOU COULD BE
AN OLYMPIAN,

00:00:21.321 --> 00:00:23.857
AND SO HE STARTS REALIZING THAT,
AND HE'S LIKE,

00:00:23.957 --> 00:00:26.827
I THINK I AM GONNA
WORK HARDER

00:00:26.927 --> 00:00:29.763
THAN YOU'VE EVER SEEN
ANYONE WORK,

00:00:29.863 --> 00:00:32.599
AND I'M GONNA BE
YOUR MOTHER[bleep].

00:00:32.699 --> 00:00:35.502
SO HE STARTS TRAINING
FOR THIS NEW EVENT,

00:00:35.602 --> 00:00:37.037
THE DECATHLON.

00:00:37.137 --> 00:00:39.940
UH...

00:00:40.040 --> 00:00:42.242
- SO HOW DID HE PREPARE?

00:00:42.342 --> 00:00:44.645
- HOW DID WHO PREPARE?
- JIM THORPE.

00:00:44.745 --> 00:00:45.913
- FOR THE OLYMPICS?

00:00:46.013 --> 00:00:47.781
HE WOULD WAKE UP
IN THE MORNING

00:00:47.881 --> 00:00:49.283
AND RUN 20 MILES,

00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:51.952
TAKE A NAP,
EAT A MILD LUNCH,

00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:57.291
AND THEN RUN
EVERY [bleep] EVENT

00:00:57.391 --> 00:00:58.692
IN THE DECATHLON.

00:00:58.792 --> 00:01:02.462
THAT IS CRAZY.

00:01:02.563 --> 00:01:03.463
[chuckles]

00:01:03.564 --> 00:01:04.865
THAT IS--

00:01:04.965 --> 00:01:06.066
[chuckles]

00:01:06.166 --> 00:01:10.037
[chuckling]
THAT IS CR-AZY.

00:01:13.140 --> 00:01:16.910 line:0%
 
1912, SWEDEN, YOU KNOW,
STOCKHOLM, SWEDEN.

00:01:17.010 --> 00:01:19.479 line:0%
 
THIS IS THE OLYMPICS.

00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:23.417 line:0%
 
THIS IS--THIS IS
THE BEST OF THE WORLD.

00:01:23.517 --> 00:01:27.821 line:0%
 
THIS AVERY BRUNDAGE GUY, IS--
WAS THE FAVORITE.

00:01:27.921 --> 00:01:29.857 line:0%
 
HE WAS A WHITE GUY,
AND HE'S LIKE,

00:01:29.957 --> 00:01:33.927 line:0%
 
I'M GONNA BE THE MAN,
THE DUDE.

00:01:34.027 --> 00:01:38.031
AND JIM THORPE WALKED IN
OUT OF NOWHERE.

00:01:38.131 --> 00:01:40.000
PEOPLE WERE LIKE,
WHAT THE [bleep]?

00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:42.135
LIKE, HOW IS HE THERE?

00:01:42.236 --> 00:01:45.873
HE'S THERE,
AND AFTER THE FIRST DAY,

00:01:45.973 --> 00:01:48.275
JIM THORPE
HAS THE POINT LEAD,

00:01:48.375 --> 00:01:51.712
AND AVERY IS LIKE,
WHAT THE [bleep]?

00:01:51.812 --> 00:01:54.181
WHO IS THIS GUY FROM?
WHO IS HE?

00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:57.684
ALL OF A SUDDEN,
THIS INDIAN IS IN THE LEAD.

00:01:57.784 --> 00:02:00.287
AVERY BRUNDAGE
IS THE FAVORITE.

00:02:00.387 --> 00:02:02.556
I MEAN, IT'S BEEN
IN THE PAPERS.

00:02:02.656 --> 00:02:06.927
IT'S BEEN
IN--IN--IN EVERYTHING.

